  "body": "In my case, i want to give 100.5 tokens for 1 ether, in such case i want to set the rate in Crowdsale.sol as 100.5. But it is accepting only whole numbers and storing only 100.\r\n\r\nYou claim to set rate only for wei to token unit, and not for ether to token\r\n\r\nBut conversion rate is always the same for any conversion.\r\n\r\nExample: If i want 100.5 tokens for 1 ether, this is same as\r\n\r\n100.5 * 10^18 units for 1 * 10^18 weis\r\n\r\nHence i somehow need conversion rate in decimals\r\n\r\nI know solidity doesnot support decimal points but how to make my case work because it is very obvious the conversion rate needs to be fluctuated in decimals based on market price",
