    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "100.5 tokens for 1 ether is *not* the same as '100.5 * 10^18 units for 1 * 10^18 weis', the decimals are only used when amounts are displayed (e.g. on exchanges), none of the math takes them into account, precisely to allow fixed point math to work.\r\n\r\nIf what you want to do is have an exchange rate of 100.5 of your token units to 1 wei, then I'm afraid that's not possible, since the EVM only supports integers: this is fundamental Ethereum design decision that cannot be worked around. ",
